text:
I had a Generate Summary Results component named "summary". It worked fine when run from the GUI, but when run from the command line, the number of requests reported were double the actual number. Renaming the Generate Summary Reports component fixed the problem.

I assume this is a bug because JMeter behaves differently depending on whether the test is run from the GUI or the command line.

Please at least include some notes in the Generate Summary Reports reference information about "summary" being a bad name.

Thanks

Hello,
> the number of requests reported were double the actual number. Renaming the Generate Summary Reports component fixed the problem.

Thank you
